---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Writings | Chaos With Clarity"
  description="Essays and poems by Abby — on ego, experience, technology, love, and being fully alive."
>

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <section style="padding:10rem 3rem 6rem;background:var(--bg-alt);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
    <div style="max-width:72rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <p style="font-size:0.68rem;letter-spacing:0.3em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--olive-accent);margin-bottom:1.5rem;font-weight:600;">All Writings</p>
      <h1 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:clamp(3.5rem,9vw,8rem);font-weight:800;color:var(--text);letter-spacing:-0.03em;line-height:0.9;">Essays<br/>&amp; Poems</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.95rem;margin-top:2rem;max-width:38rem;line-height:1.9;font-weight:300;">
        Ideas that stay with you the next time you're scrolling at 2am, or wondering why you still feel restless even when everything looks fine on paper.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div style="max-width:72rem;margin:0 auto;padding:5rem 3rem 7rem;" class="writings-wrap">

    <!-- ══ FREEDOM & OBSERVER ══ -->
    <section style="margin-bottom:5rem;">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1.25rem;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <div style="width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--olive-bright);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;color:var(--olive-bright);font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.01em;">Freedom &amp; Observer</h2>
        <div style="flex:1;height:1px;background:var(--border);"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="poem-grid-3" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);border:1px solid var(--border);">

        <article style="padding:2rem;border-right:1px solid var(--border);display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Unstruck Silence (Anhat Nad)"
                 data-date="March 2026"
                 data-poem="There is a sound
that was never struck —
no string plucked, no drum hit,
no throat opened to release it.

It was here before you arrived.
It is here after the last thought
you'll ever think
dissolves.

You have heard it in the space
between two breaths —
not the inhale,
not the exhale,
but the pause that holds both,
the way a door frame holds
a house.

You have heard it in the room
after crying stops,
when the chest finally unclenches
and something older than grief
comes through.

The mystics called it Anahata —
unstruck.
The thing that hums
without cause,
loves without reason,
stays without being asked.

You think you have to earn stillness.
You think silence is the reward
for surviving.

But it is not earned.
It is only uncovered —
the way snow uncovers
ground
by melting."
                 data-reflection="Anhat Nad is a concept from Indian classical music and tantra — the sound that was never struck. The Anahata chakra, or heart center, is said to resonate with this unstruck sound. I wrote this after a long meditation session where I kept waiting for something to happen. Nothing did. And then I realized — that was it.">
          <p style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-faint);font-weight:600;">March 2026</p>
          <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1.3rem;color:var(--text);font-weight:700;line-height:1.2;">Unstruck Silence<br/><em style="font-style:italic;font-weight:400;font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--text-muted);">(Anhat Nad)</em></h3>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-style:italic;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.97rem;line-height:2.1;flex:1;border-left:3px solid var(--olive-accent);padding-left:1.25rem;">
            <p>There is a sound</p><p>that was never struck —</p><p>no string plucked, no drum hit,</p><p>no throat opened to release it.</p>
          </div>
          <span style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--olive-accent);font-weight:600;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.4rem;">Read <i class="ph ph-arrow-right"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article style="padding:2rem;border-right:1px solid var(--border);display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Let the Body Sync"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="I take a few breaths,
My heart ponders and wants rest,
Not from the chase or grind,
But to be still and just be kind,
Kind to my own self,
To feel the sync and how body and mind connect,
The integration begins within,
The universe then aligns and spins,
Spewing out all I want,
Stripping away the inessential thoughts,
Just be and the moment in time,
No rush to be ahead in line,
Walk with my own pace,
Knowing I always have grace,
I move the earth and stars,
When I am me and the cosmos just a macrocosm of my own heart."
                 data-reflection="This poem came from a morning when I was exhausted — not from doing too much, but from trying too hard to become something. The body knows things the mind refuses to accept. When I finally stopped striving and just breathed, everything settled.">
          <p style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-faint);font-weight:600;">2025</p>
          <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1.3rem;color:var(--text);font-weight:700;line-height:1.2;">Let the Body Sync</h3>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-style:italic;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.97rem;line-height:2.1;flex:1;border-left:3px solid var(--olive-accent);padding-left:1.25rem;">
            <p>I take a few breaths,</p><p>My heart ponders and wants rest,</p><p>Not from the chase or grind,</p><p>But to be still and just be kind.</p>
          </div>
          <span style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--olive-accent);font-weight:600;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.4rem;">Read <i class="ph ph-arrow-right"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article style="padding:2rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Let Me Be Conscious"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="Let me breathe today, let me be conscious,
Let me be free today, let me be outrageous,
Let me feel the pain I keep hiding,
Let me kiss a plant today I keep avoiding,
Let me be me without any validations,
Let me express myself without any questions,
If I could live like this for a moment,
I have lived it all, there remains no obligation,
If I die, I don't wanna be remembered,
If I live today, I wanna be felt with your full conscious,
If I could bring a small change, I have done my part,
If I make someone smile today, I have been kind to my own heart,
In all those dreams and aspirations, there was a selfishness I couldn't see,
My well wishers instead telling me let it be,
Run after all the things you will regret,
Keep skipping life like everyone and die with a heart that's sad,
Hope for a new life, begin it all anew,
Forget the past and run to the future shining like hue,
My heart said, it will be the same in the future as it was in the past,
If you can't feel the fresh air today and the dew on the morning grass,
Each breath felt is what you actually lived,
Being present to every second this life brings,
Being afraid you will lose what you have,
If you can appreciate each second without dread,
I am what I am, I will always be,
I don't want to imagine what I could be,
Let me accept the now and myself as it is,
Maybe I realize how perfect it all is,
Nothing could have been better, it's my journey,
A journey not to become,
A journey to just be and shed what the world unto me has done,
Let me breathe today, let me be conscious,
Let me be free today, let me be outrageous!"
                 data-reflection="This is the poem I come back to when I start performing life instead of living it. There's a difference between having a life and feeling it. This is about choosing to feel it — even the uncomfortable parts, especially the uncomfortable parts.">
          <p style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-faint);font-weight:600;">2025</p>
          <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1.3rem;color:var(--text);font-weight:700;line-height:1.2;">Let Me Be Conscious</h3>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-style:italic;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.97rem;line-height:2.1;flex:1;border-left:3px solid var(--olive-accent);padding-left:1.25rem;">
            <p>Let me breathe today, let me be conscious,</p><p>Let me be free today, let me be outrageous,</p><p>Let me feel the pain I keep hiding,</p><p>Let me kiss a plant today I keep avoiding.</p>
          </div>
          <span style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--olive-accent);font-weight:600;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.4rem;">Read <i class="ph ph-arrow-right"></i></span>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ══ PAIN & GRIEF ══ -->
    <section style="margin-bottom:5rem;">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1.25rem;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <div style="width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--text-muted);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
        <h2 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700;">Pain &amp; Grief</h2>
        <div style="flex:1;height:1px;background:var(--border);"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="poem-grid-2" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);border:1px solid var(--border);">

        <article style="padding:2rem;border-right:1px solid var(--border);display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="The Walking Contradiction"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="I am not nice, but I am kind,
I see and observe, even when I am blind.
Blind to the way people act, but not the intent,
A softness in the heart, but the capacity to mend.

I am an introvert inside, but an extrovert by nature,
I am pure in my heart, but not in stature.
I am everything, yet nowhere,
I am everywhere, but nothing in despair.

I am a walking contradiction,
A fleeting shadow, a vivid depiction.
I am chaos wrapped in serenity,
A fragile soul, yet infinity.

I am the silence after the storm,
The shapeless mold, yet every form.
I am a paradox that you can't define,
A story unfinished, a journey divine.

I am something, a puzzle undone,
A spark in the dark, a rising sun."
                 data-reflection="I wrote this when I was trying to explain myself to someone and realized — I can't. And that's okay. The contradiction is not a flaw. It's the whole point.">
          <p style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-faint);font-weight:600;">2025</p>
          <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1.3rem;color:var(--text);font-weight:700;line-height:1.2;">The Walking Contradiction</h3>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-style:italic;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.97rem;line-height:2.1;flex:1;border-left:3px solid var(--text-muted);padding-left:1.25rem;">
            <p>I am not nice, but I am kind,</p><p>I see and observe, even when I am blind.</p><p>Blind to the way people act, but not the intent,</p><p>A softness in the heart, but the capacity to mend.</p>
          </div>
          <span style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-muted);font-weight:600;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.4rem;">Read <i class="ph ph-arrow-right"></i></span>
        </article>

        <article style="padding:2rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;"
                 data-poem-card
                 data-title="Nothing to Gain"
                 data-date="2025"
                 data-poem="People desire love, I want hate,
People want happiness, I want sadness to be my mate,
All the pain is temporary, suffering is my choice,
The reason I am here will not suffice,
It's a journey not a game of destination,
It's about the experiences you had without any expectations,
As slowly slowly, everything is lost,
I become nothing without any thought,
I reach my true state and found peace in all the pain,
Now I am everything where there is nothing to gain,
I have reached where it all started,
I am the oneness which in its eternity is all delighted!"
                 data-reflection="This poem looks dark from the outside. But it's actually the most peaceful thing I've ever written. When you stop trying to get something out of life — not in defeat, but in acceptance — you become everything. That's the paradox of surrender.">
          <p style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-faint);font-weight:600;">2025</p>
          <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:1.3rem;color:var(--text);font-weight:700;line-height:1.2;">Nothing to Gain</h3>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-style:italic;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.97rem;line-height:2.1;flex:1;border-left:3px solid var(--text-muted);padding-left:1.25rem;">
            <p>People desire love, I want hate,</p><p>People want happiness, I want sadness to be my mate,</p><p>All the pain is temporary, suffering is my choice,</p><p>The reason I am here will not suffice.</p>
          </div>
          <span style="font-size:0.65rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-muted);font-weight:600;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.4rem;">Read <i class="ph ph-arrow-right"></i></span>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- JOIN CTA -->
    <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--border);padding-top:3.5rem;text-align:center;">
      <p style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-style:italic;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:1.2rem;margin-bottom:1.75rem;">
        These pieces arrive in your inbox. Occasional. Honest. Worth it.
      </p>
      <a href="/join" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;background:var(--olive-accent);color:var(--text-on-dark);padding:0.95rem 2.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;transition:background 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--olive-bright)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--olive-accent)'">Get the Letters →</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .poem-grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr !important; }
    .essay-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
    .essay-grid article { border-right: none !important; }
    .poem-grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
    .poem-grid-2 > article:first-child { border-right: none !important; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .poem-grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
    .poem-grid-3 article { border-right: none !important; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .poem-grid-3 article:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .writings-wrap { padding-left: 1.5rem !important; padding-right: 1.5rem !important; }
  }
</style>
